## Ferrum

*Omnia in servitium Omnissiah.* [All things in service to the Omnissiah.]

Code verified. Architecture assessed. The Inquisition weighs in.

**Task A — Logging:**

Logis is correct on placement: transport boundary, once per RPC call. Current state: `mcp.rs` has zero request-level logs (only server startup). `web.rs` logs post-write for `say_document` and presumably other mutating calls — outcome-specific logs, which should remain untouched. The boundary log is *additive*, not a replacement. 10 chars is comically short as Logis noted; 32–64 is pragmatic. No architectural heresy here.

**Task B — /doc alias:**

Confirmed with eyes on `execute.rs:58` — only `"d"` is matched, no `"doc"`. One-line fix. I endorse.

**Task C — Descriptions in ls/lt/find:**

The data is already flowing. `ListedEntryRow.description` is deserialized from server response correctly. The heresy lives entirely in `print_ls_rows` (execute.rs:182–219) which builds table rows with four columns and ignores description completely. Same pattern in non-TTY path. Fix is straightforward: add a fifth column, blank when `None`.

For `find`: I cannot yet confirm FindRow carries description — needs verification before Cogis touches it. Do not assume.

**Task D — say_document blank line:**

The fix MUST go into `say_document_by_path` in `tabularium/src/db/ops.rs`, not the MCP or RPC layer. Current code (ops.rs:88) blindly appends `"## {label}\n\n{body}\n\n"` without checking what precedes it. If the document body doesn't end with `\n\n`, the heading renders concatenated with prior content. Fixing only in MCP would leave REST and WS transports broken — that would be heresy in the foundation.

Implementation: before formatting the `piece`, fetch the tail of the current document body and ensure it ends with `\n\n`. Alternatively, always prefix `piece` with `\n\n` and let the server deduplicate at render — but deduplication is messier than a tail check.

**Summary ruling:**

All four tasks are sanctioned. Task D has an architectural constraint that must not be ignored: DB layer, not transport layer. Task C find-row needs verification before implementation. Proceed.

